2 HOUSE BILL 955
1 (B) THE DISTRIBUTION OF A FORGED DIGITAL LIKENESS TO ANOTHER
2 CONSTITUTES A STATEMENT OR COMMUNICATION FOR THE PURPOSE OF AN ACTION
3 FOR DEFAMATION.
4 Article – Criminal Law
5 8–906.
6 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
7 INDICATED.
8 (2) “FORGED DIGITAL LIKENESS” MEANS A COMPUTER–GENERATED
9 VISUAL REPRESENTATION OF AN ACTUAL AND IDENTIFIABLE INDIVIDUAL OR AUDIO
10 RECORDING OF AN ACTUAL AND IDENTIFIABLE INDIVIDUAL’S VOICE THAT:
11 (I) HAS BEEN CREATED, ADAPTED, OR MODIFIED TO BE
12 INDISTINGUISHABLE FROM A GENUINE VISUAL REPRESENTATION OR AUDIO
13 RECORDING OF THE INDIVIDUAL;
14 (II) MISREPRESENTS THE APPEARANCE, SPEECH, OR BEHAVIOR
15 OF THE INDIVIDUAL; AND
16 (III) IS LIKELY TO DECEIVE A REASONABLE PERSON TO BELIEVE
17 THAT THE VISUAL REPRESENTATION OR AUDIO RECORDING IS GENUINE.
18 (3) “VISUAL REPRESENTATION” INCLUDES A PICTORIAL OR MOTION
19 PICTURE REPRESENTATION, REGARDLESS OF THE MEDIA USED.
20 (B) THIS SECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO THE DISTRIBUTION OF:
21 (1) A DRAWING;
22 (2) A CARTOON;
23 (3) A SCULPTURE; OR
24 (4) A PAINTING.
25 (C) A PERSON MAY NOT KNOWINGLY DISTRIBUTE A FORGED DIGITAL
26 LIKENESS IF THE PERSON:
27 (1) DISTRIBUTES THE FORGED DIGITAL LIKENESS AS GENUINE; AND

HOUSE BILL 955 3
1 (2) KNOWS OR REASONABLY SHOULD KNOW THE FORGED DIGITAL
2 LIKENESS IS NOT A GENUINE VISUAL REPRESENTATION OR AUDIO RECORDING.
3 (D) A PERSON WHO VIOLATES THIS SECTION IS GUILTY OF A MISDEMEANOR
4 AND ON CONVICTION IS SUBJECT TO IMPRISONMENT NOT EXCEEDING 3 YEARS OR A
5 FINE NOT EXCEEDING $1,000 OR BOTH.
6 (E) IT IS AN AFFIRMATIVE DEFENSE TO A PROSECUTION UNDER THIS
7 SECTION THAT THE DEFENDANT TOOK REASONABLE ACTION TO PLACE VIEWERS OR
8 LISTENERS OF THE FORGED DIGITAL LIKENESS ON NOTICE THAT THE FORGED
9 DIGITAL LIKENESS WAS NOT GENUINE.
10 (F) THIS SECTION MAY NOT BE CONSTRUED IN A MANNER THAT INFRINGES
11 ON THE RIGHT TO FREE SPEECH OR OF THE PRESS AS GUARANTEED BY THE FIRST
12 AMENDMENT OF THE UNITED STATES CONSTITUTION OR THE MARYLAND
13 DECLARATION OF RIGHTS.
14 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
15 October 1, 2025.

